Dialogue: Have we heard that?
It is rather – pungent.
Actually, Rome, the wise heads feel the Maniacs are in fact only
clinging on. The Maniacs are the moderating influence right
now.
Yeah. You have a small country-club rump but the Maniac
Majority are really a good option.
If anything we need to bolster the Maniacs. Because they’re
getting outflanked by the nutjobs, who are losing ground to the
full-on shit-flinging fuckheads. Our best hope is finding what I
think of as a ‘capable maniac’.
Don’t worry, Greg, it’s nice. It’s a safe space where you don’t
have to pretend to like Hamilton.
Sure you do. We all do.
Ooh I don’t know, Greg. Maybe we should phone the referee?
Is there an ombudsman in the house?
Shame what happened. Although? There is the argument, the
prez was no longer in the same place as the party?
But he did go very easy on Big Tech. Gotta get a hold of that?
Really? No, I think I’ve seen him eat a meatball.
Broach away, Greg.
Are you threatening me? Because you can’t threaten me. I’m
immune.
Yeah I tried that – it doesn’t work. What I’m preferring, is to
always think about it. Then when you don’t for a moment it’s
like, ‘Oooh, someone’s loosened their icy grip on my innards’?
Uh-huh so, you wanna try? It’s the Spätburgunder. From our
vineyard.
Oh. Screwtop?
Uh-huh. It’s biodynamic, so—
it has a definite funk to it.
Yeah you have to meet it halfway.
Interesting. I feel like it’s still unfolding, in my mouth. Yeah,
atmospheric. A little gothic. Definitely Old World. It’s old. It’s –
it’s, it’s, it’s – it’s—
it’s not very nice, is it, Shiv?
Yeah, my prison consultant called. It’s looking like the place
upstate might be full.
Yeah? One day closer to my incarceration.
They’re all the same.
They say the food is—
I’m sorry, does the topic of my imminent imprisonment bore
you?
Sure.
There just doesn’t seem much point?
If you’re still on contraception?
It’s just – throwing so much cake batter at a brick wall?
Waffle time, Sporus. C’mon. I’m gonna teach you about prison.
So, according to Steven, my prison consultant, apparently this
is what the food is like, you know, inside. So I’m in training. How
is the omelette?
It’s like Afghanistan.
Establish a base of operation in the center there and work out
to secure more territory.
It won’t be as good as this of course. Take off thirty to fifty
percent of the endless salty gym mat. The camel’s labia.
Obviously. I have read all the blogs, Greg.
What’s good is to eradicate hope. Hope is the enemy. If you
can drain that away, then they can’t get you, because you’ve
got no hope, you see?
I haven’t slept in eight days.
Are you asking if you can hook your bauble of corporate
wrongdoing to one of my branches, Greg?
Fine. Load me up you piece of shit.
Giddy up. Load up the crime mule.
Nah. Greenpeace stole your inheritance. Besides, all my meals
will be free soon.
Okay. Greg, will you keep a note?
Yeah. Your toilet could be a bastard?
Me, I think – I think Shiv talks a lot of sense. I also jibe with
Salgado.
Um, excuse me—
Hello?
Uh-huh?
Um, Virginia? Why?
Please. Hugo. Understood.
Cyd! Excuse me. Duty calls!
I can’t be seen with you. I know a place—
Hey. The griddle hero special. Double hash browns, fully
loaded. Plain waffle and a large cup of room-temperature water.
You know Rasputin would take a dose of arsenic with breakfast
each morning, to build up tolerance.
I like you too, Kendall. I mean, I have notes.
I think mine might be more extensive.
Uh-huh? Well nothing is certain, so.
Perhaps it’s because I’m tall and jolly?
Well obviously I’d prefer that not to happen. But it’s
complicated.
I have, of late, decided not to tarry much with hope.
Oh I don’t know if I do know that?
I’m just a humble servant.
Well shucks. Thank you. I fell in love with your sister, is what
happened.
I guess.
Wow. Suddenly everyone wants to buy me dinner?
So, thanks for the waffles.
Let me think.
You know prison was my idea. Not Shiv’s. Not Logan’s. Mine.
Shiv’s a warrior.
And how exactly do you think it works if I come over? How is it
better when I tell my wife, who I love, and this family, that I’m
turning against them?
You make some sense.
But – and I don’t want to be insulting, but having been around a
bit, my hunch is you’re going to get fucked. Because I’ve seen
you get fucked a lot and I’ve never seen Logan get fucked
once.
Would I be happier being yours?
Great. Classy. I have to get back.
You know what they’re doing in his suite? They’re picking the
next president.
Let me ponder a moment.
So I saw you. You looked like you were having a whale of a
time up there? Flying on the wings of white power?
Did it feel good, when the fascists hoisted you up like the
Stanley Cup?
I’m kidding, Greg. You can’t. You can’t change people’s minds.
Greg, shut up. Give people what they want, then walk away.
After that, it’s their shit.
